\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Select the Key Signature Tool.  Click on a staff to place the key signature where the pointer is.  The selection area of a key signature is any location within the bounding box of the key signature.  Unless overridden by a TOOL button, the default key signature is one flat cancelled.  This is chosen for the default because it has no effect.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\keepn\fi0\sb240\sa80\li0\ri0\f2\fs32\b1\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\b Key signature placement\b0  \par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 As for any staff object, key signatures are automatically placed when the system is adjusted (see \b Adjustment\b0 ).  To otherwise move a key signature,  select the key signature and hold the mouse button down to drag the key signature to a desired location.  The key signature attaches itself to the nearest staff.  The signs making up the signature rearrange themselves depending on the type of nearest controlling clef.  Ledger lines are drawn automatically if necessary.  To move the key signature up or down in staff degree relative to its governing clef (thus changing the pitch centre in a way unsanctioned by proper sequence in the circle of fifths), hold down the ALT button while dragging the key signature.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 \par
